-- Vinci Partners May Invest $284 Million in Insurance, Valor Economico Says
-- Laura Price
-- 2010-07-15T10:44:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/vinci-may-invest-500-million-reais-in-insurance-valor-economico-reports.html

          
          
             Vinci Partners, a Brazilian
investment company set up by Gilberto Sayao, a former partner at
Banco Pactual, may invest as much as 500 million reais ($284
million) in two insurance companies within five years, Valor
Economico reported, citing a partner at Vinci.      
 Vinci is creating Austral Seguradora, an insurer for
engineering projects, and Austral Resseguradora, which will
operate in all areas of insurance, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper
said, citing Alessandro Horta.   
